[0m[49m[39m  138, 156[0m:[39m[49m ### Prerequisites
[0m[49m[39m  139, 157[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  140, 158[0m:[39m[49m | Requirement | Details |
[0m[49m[39m  141, 159[0m:[39m[49m |-------------|---------|
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 142     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **AWS Services** | Amazon Comprehend Medical, Amazon SageMaker, Amazon S3, Amazon DynamoDB, AWS Lambda, Amazon API Gateway |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 143     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **IAM Permissions** | `comprehend-medical:DetectEntitiesV2`, `comprehend-medical:InferICD10CM`, `sagemaker:InvokeEndpoint`, `s3:GetObject`, `s3:PutObject`, `dynamodb:GetItem`, `dynamodb:Query` |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 144     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **BAA** | AWS BAA signed (required: clinical notes contain PHI) |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 145     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Encryption** | S3: SSE-KMS; DynamoDB: encryption at rest (default); SageMaker endpoint: inter-container encryption; Lambda CloudWatch logs: KMS encryption; all API calls over TLS |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 146     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **VPC** | Production: Lambda in VPC with VPC endpoints for S3, Comprehend Medical, SageMaker, DynamoDB, and CloudWatch Logs |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 147     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **CloudTrail** | Enabled: log all Comprehend Medical, SageMaker invoke, and S3 access for HIPAA audit |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 148     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Training Data** | Historical encounter notes paired with finalized ICD-10 codes. Minimum 50,000 encounters recommended. De-identified for model development; BAA-covered processing for production. |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 149     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Cost Estimate** | Comprehend Medical DetectEntitiesV2: ~$0.01 per 100 characters (a typical note is 2,000-5,000 chars = $0.20-0.50 per note). InferICD10CM: similar pricing. SageMaker real-time endpoint: ml.m5.xlarge ~$0.23/hr. Lambda/DynamoDB negligible at this scale. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS Services** | Amazon Comprehend Medical, AWS Lambda, Amazon API Gateway, Amazon DynamoDB, Amazon S3, AWS KMS, Amazon CloudWatch |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      161[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **IAM Permissions** | `comprehend:InferICD10CM`, `comprehend:DetectEntitiesV2`, `dynamodb:PutItem`, `dynamodb:GetItem`, `s3:PutObject`, `s3:GetObject`, `kms:Decrypt`, `kms:GenerateDataKey` |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      162[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **BAA** | AWS BAA signed. Comprehend Medical, Lambda, DynamoDB, S3, API Gateway, and CloudWatch are all HIPAA-eligible services. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      163[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Encryption** | S3: SSE-KMS with customer-managed key. DynamoDB: encryption at rest (default). API Gateway: TLS 1.2 in transit. Lambda environment variables encrypted with KMS. CloudWatch log groups: configure KMS encryption (logs may contain clinical text fragments). |
