[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 173     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m **Step 1: Receive and preprocess the clinical note.** When a coder opens an encounter in their worklist, the coding tool sends the clinical note to your API. The first step is cleaning the text for NLP processing. Clinical notes have structure that helps and structure that hurts: section headers help you weight the Assessment/Plan section more heavily; copy-forward boilerplate from prior visits hurts because it introduces stale information. This preprocessing step segments the note, identifies the highest-value sections, and normalizes common abbreviations. Skip this and your model gets confused by noise, especially template text that appears in every note regardless of the patient's conditions.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      186[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 1: Receive and preprocess the clinical note.** Notes arrive from the EHR via API call (synchronous workflow for real-time suggestions in the coding UI) or via a batch file drop (async workflow for overnight processing). The preprocessing step segments the note into clinically relevant sections and identifies the highest-value text for code suggestion. The Assessment and Plan section contains the most explicitly codable content. The Problem List is often a bulleted list of active diagnoses. Sending the entire 5,000-word note to Comprehend Medical works, but it's expensive and introduces noise from review-of-systems negations and template boilerplate.
[0m[49m[39m  174, 187[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  175, 188[0m:[39m[49m ```pseudocode
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      189[0m:[38;5;10m[49m // Section headers commonly found in clinical notes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      190[0m:[38;5;10m[49m // The Assessment/Plan section is the richest source of codable diagnoses.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      191[0m:[38;5;10m[49m // We prioritize these sections but fall back to full text if sections aren't detected.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      192[0m:[38;5;10m[49m PRIORITY_SECTIONS = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      193[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "assessment and plan",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "assessment/plan",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "assessment",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "plan",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "diagnoses",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "problem list",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "impression",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "discharge diagnoses"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m SECONDARY_SECTIONS = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "history of present illness",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "hpi",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "hospital course"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  176, 209[0m:[39m[49m FUNCTION preprocess_note(raw_note_text):
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 177     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // Clinical notes have predictable section headers (HPI, ROS, Assessment, Plan, etc.)
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 178     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // The Assessment and Plan sections carry the most coding-relevant information.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 179     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // Other sections (vitals, review of systems) are useful but noisier.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 180     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Attempt to segment the note by section headers.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Clinical notes typically use headers like "ASSESSMENT AND PLAN:" or "HPI:"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // followed by a colon or newline.
[0m[49m[39m  181, 213[0m:[39m[49m     sections = segment_by_headers(raw_note_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 182     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // segment_by_headers splits on known patterns like "ASSESSMENT:", "A/P:", "PLAN:"
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 183     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 184     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // Weight sections by coding relevance:
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 185     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // Assessment/Plan = primary signal
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 186     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // History of Present Illness = secondary signal
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 187     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // Medications/Problem List = supporting evidence
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 188     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // Review of Systems = mostly negated findings (still useful for ruling things out)
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 189     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 190     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     priority_text = concatenate sections in order:
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 191     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         sections["assessment_plan"]       // highest coding signal
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 192     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         sections["hpi"]                   // describes current conditions
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 193     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         sections["problem_list"]          // explicit condition list
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 194     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         sections["medications"]           // implies conditions being treated
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 195     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 196     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // Normalize abbreviations that confuse NLP models
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 197     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // "HTN" -> "hypertension", "DM2" -> "type 2 diabetes", "CHF" -> "congestive heart failure"
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 198     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     normalized_text = expand_abbreviations(priority_text, CLINICAL_ABBREV_MAP)
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 199     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 200     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // Remove copy-forward artifacts: text blocks identical to prior encounters.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 201     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // These introduce stale conditions that may no longer apply.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 202     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     // In production, compare against the patient's last 3-5 notes to detect copy-forward.
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 203     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     cleaned_text = remove_duplicate_blocks(normalized_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 204     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 205     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m     RETURN cleaned_text
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // If we found recognizable sections, extract priority content.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     IF sections is not empty:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         priority_text = ""
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         secondary_text = ""
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         FOR each section_name, section_content in sections:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             normalized_name = lowercase(trim(section_name))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             IF normalized_name matches any in PRIORITY_SECTIONS:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 priority_text = priority_text + " " + section_content
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             ELSE IF normalized_name matches any in SECONDARY_SECTIONS:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 secondary_text = secondary_text + " " + section_content
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Use priority text if available; fall back to secondary; last resort is full text.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         IF length(priority_text) > 50:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             coding_text = trim(priority_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ELSE IF length(secondary_text) > 50:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             coding_text = trim(secondary_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ELSE:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             coding_text = trim(raw_note_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ELSE:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // No section headers detected. Use the full note.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         coding_text = trim(raw_note_text)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Comprehend Medical InferICD10CM accepts up to 10,000 UTF-8 characters.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Truncate at sentence boundary if we exceed the limit.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     IF length(coding_text) > 9500:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         coding_text = truncate_at_sentence_boundary(coding_text, 9500)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     RETURN coding_text
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Step 2: Call InferICD10CM for code candidates.** This is the core inference step. We send the preprocessed clinical text to Comprehend Medical's ICD-10 inference API and receive back a structured response containing entities (spans of text that map to diagnostic concepts) and their associated ICD-10-CM code candidates ranked by confidence.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```pseudocode
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m // Confidence thresholds for different suggestion tiers.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m // High-confidence suggestions are presented as "recommended" to the coder.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m // Medium-confidence suggestions are presented as "possible" alternatives.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m // Below the minimum threshold, we don't surface the suggestion at all.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m HIGH_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD = 0.80
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m MEDIUM_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD = 0.50
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m MINIMUM_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD = 0.30
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m // Maximum number of candidate codes to return per entity.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m MAX_CANDIDATES_PER_ENTITY = 5
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FUNCTION infer_icd10_codes(coding_text):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     // Call the Comprehend Medical InferICD10CM API.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = call ComprehendMedical.InferICD10CM with:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Text = coding_text
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     suggestions = empty list
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     FOR each entity in response.Entities:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // entity.Text = the span of clinical text that triggered this entity
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // entity.Category = always "MEDICAL_CONDITION" for InferICD10CM
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // entity.Traits = assertion modifiers (NEGATION, SIGN, SYMPTOM, DIAGNOSIS)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // entity.ICD10CMConcepts = ranked list of code candidates
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Check assertion traits: skip negated concepts.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         is_negated = any trait in entity.Traits where trait.Name == "NEGATION" and trait.Score >= 0.75
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         IF is_negated:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             CONTINUE    // "No diabetes" should not suggest diabetes codes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Check for SIGN vs DIAGNOSIS trait.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Signs/symptoms get coded differently than confirmed diagnoses.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         is_sign_or_symptom = any trait in entity.Traits where trait.Name in ["SIGN", "SYMPTOM"] and trait.Score >= 0.75
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         is_diagnosis = any trait in entity.Traits where trait.Name == "DIAGNOSIS" and trait.Score >= 0.75
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         // Process code candidates.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         candidates = empty list
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         FOR each concept in entity.ICD10CMConcepts (up to MAX_CANDIDATES_PER_ENTITY):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             IF concept.Score < MINIMUM_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 BREAK   // candidates are sorted by score; once below minimum, stop
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             tier = "low"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             IF concept.Score >= HIGH_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 tier = "high"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             ELSE IF concept.Score >= MEDIUM_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD:
